item.title: About
item.description: RPAA Board of Directors The RPAA is a statewide organization, which is recognized by USA Racquetball (USAR) as the governing body of racquetball in Arizona. All Board members are non-compensated volunteers that are elected by the active RPAA membership for three year terms. A Few Words About Us The RPAA is responsible for sanctioning tournaments in Arizona under the guidelines set forth by the USAR. The aims and objectives of the RPAA are as follows:
